4.css selector
use id as the hook!
<li id="special">
		<input type="checkbox">
		Finish Recording CSS Videos
	</li>
 each id can only show up once! ( you can't have another special
 
 --- in the css file (#)
   #special{
	    background: yellow;
   }

class : can apply to an elements in a page
	<li class="completed">
		<input type="checkbox" checked>
		Walk Rusty
	</li>
	<li class="completed">
		<input type="checkbox" checked>
		Buy Groceries
	</li>
--- in the css file (.)
.completed {
	text-decoration: line-through;
}

