}


5.inheritance and specificity in CSS
you have ul and li, when you change ul , li is also changed, since li is in ul
when you set parent, the child will also change

the more/specific close one wins!
MDN tells you how to pick (runs a calculation)
--specificty calculator
usually id is the most specific

li < li a < li +a < .hello = input[type = "text"] < #spec


